{"article_id":"DVoQgfvqv9UImzKU","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Round 2 : Health Care Law Faces The Supreme Court Again","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Round 2 in the legal battle over Obamacare hits the Supreme Court 's intellectual boxing ring Wednesday .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"In one corner is the Obama administration ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"backed by the nation 's hospitals , insurance companies , physician associations and other groups like Catholic Charities and the American Cancer Society .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"In the other corner are conservative groups ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"backed by politicians","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"who fought in Congress","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"to prevent the bill from being adopted .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"In 2012 , a bitterly divided high court upheld the law as constitutional by a 5-to-4 vote .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Now opponents of the law are challenging it again ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"this time contending","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that the text of the law does not authorize subsidies","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"to make mandated insurance affordable in 34 states .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"It 's a technical argument about the wording of the law","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"but ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"if it prevails ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"most experts say","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"the result would be a chaotic unraveling of a system","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"that in the past year has extended health insurance to more than 11 million Americans .","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"The fight is about six pesky words in one section of the law .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Those words stipulate","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"that for people","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"who can not afford health coverage ,","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"subsidies are available through `` an exchange","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"established by the state . ''","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"The government contends","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that those words refer to any exchange ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"whether it is set up by the state itself or an exchange","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"run for the state by the federal government in accordance with individual state insurance laws and regulations .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"The challengers say","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"the statute means what it says and no more .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"If the Supreme Court agrees with the challengers ' interpretation ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"millions of people would quickly lose their health insurance","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"and the individual insurance market could collapse in 34 states .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"Those 34 are the states , mainly Republican-run ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"that declined to set up an exchange themselves .","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"A few other states also found","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"that the system","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"they created on their own","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"did n't work well","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"and so opted instead to use the federally run system .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"Every major regulatory law like the Affordable Care Act is carried out","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"according to regulations","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"issued by appropriate agencies .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"And the Internal Revenue Service issued this regulation ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"that subsidies would be available to people","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"who signed up on exchanges in every state ,","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"whether state-run or federally run .","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"`` We do n't treat members of Congress like teenage adolescents","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"who do n't know","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"what they 're saying . ''","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"That was the whole design of the law ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"the IRS says ,","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"noting","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"that Congress never even discussed limiting subsidies to state-run exchanges .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"`` Ridiculous , ''","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"says the lawyer for the challengers , Michael Carvin .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"`` The text says precisely the opposite of what these English-speaking people purportedly intended . ''","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"`` It says ,","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"you get subsidies","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"if you make a purchase on an exchange","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"established by the state , ''","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"says Carvin ,","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"but the IRS wrote a rule","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"authorizing subsidies for federally run exchanges as well .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"Former Obama administration Solicitor General Neal Katyal ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"who filed a brief in the case on behalf of the nation 's major hospital groups ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"disagrees .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"`` You can take a phrase out of any statute","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"and twist it","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"to mean something else , ''","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"he says .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Katyal emphasizes","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"that a basic maxim","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"of interpreting statutes","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"is to look at the overall structure and purpose of the act .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"`` It 's notable , ''","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"he says ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"`` that in all the thousands of pages of briefing","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"that the Affordable Care Act challengers have put together ,","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"they ca n't find a single member of Congress at any point in the many debates of the Affordable Care Act","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"who believes","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"what these lawyers are saying .","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"Not one . ''","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Indeed , even Republicans did seem to assume","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"that the subsidies went to everyone","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"who needed them ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"regardless of where they lived .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"Rep. Paul Ryan , the top Republican on the House Budget Committee , said in 2010 ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"`` It 's a new and open-ended entitlement","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"that basically says , to just about everybody in this country :","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"If your health care expenses exceed anywhere from 2 to 9.8 percent of your adjusted gross income ...","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"do n't worry about it ...","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"the government 's going to subsidize the rest . ''","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"Wisconsin Gov . Scott Walker , a leading Republican , also seemed to assume","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"that the subsidies would go to everyone .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"`` In the end , there 's no real substantive difference between a federal exchange or a state exchange , ''","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"Walker once said .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"Although some of the challengers initially portrayed their case as involving a drafting error or `` glitch , ''","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"Carvin says","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"the language","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"restricting subsidies to state-run exchanges","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"was deliberate .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"`` We do n't treat members of Congress like teenage adolescents","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"who do n't know","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"what they 're saying , ''","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"says Carvin .","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"`` The only people","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"who ever said","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"it was a drafting glitch","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"were liberal polemicists","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"who are trying to deny the force of the statute , not us . ''","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"Carvin notes","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"that those words","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"limiting subsidies to `` an exchange","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"established by the state ''","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"actually appear in the statute 11 times .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"Congress was acting rationally and intentionally","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"when it used those words ,","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"he maintains ,","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"because the whole idea was to provide incentives","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"for states to set up exchanges themselves .","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"`` They wanted subsidies","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"and they wanted state-run exchanges , ''","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"Carvin contends .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"`` If you condition the subsidies ,","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"you get both .","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"If you give unconditional subsidies ,","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"you do n't get state-run exchanges . ''","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"Not so ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"says former Health and Human Services Secretary Kathleen Sebelius ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"who argues","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"the conditional subsidy idea would lead to `` absurd results . ''","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"`` You would have in place a national rule","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"that says","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"no company could ban people with a pre-existing condition ;","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"you would have a national rule","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"that says","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"everybody has to have coverage ;","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"and then you would have millions of people","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"who would have no affordable way","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"to get that coverage , ''","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"she says .","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"What 's more , Sebelius contends","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"that a conditional plan such as the one","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"Carvin outlines","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"would amount to bait-and-switch for the states .","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"`` As one","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"who was not only at the table","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"when the law was being designed","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"and at the front end of a lot of conversations with states , ''","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"she says ,","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"`` I can tell you","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"that there was never a design","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"that suggested to governors or state leaders","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"that somehow ,","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"if they did not have a state-based marketplace ,","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"they would lose tax subsidies for their constituents . ''","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"But what would happen","depth":8},{"id":160,"text":"if the Supreme Court does n't buy that argument","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"and instead knocks a huge hole in the law ?","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"Estimates are that 9.3 million people","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"who get subsidies now through Obamacare in those 34 states","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"would lose about $ 29 billion in subsidies","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"and would not be able to afford coverage .","depth":7},{"id":166,"text":"In addition , experts say","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"that disallowing the subsidies in the states with federal exchanges would destabilize the individual insurance market in those states ,","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"meaning that rates would skyrocket for individuals and many small businesses","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"that currently buy policies independent of the federal exchange .","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"Karen Ignagni ,","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"who heads the association","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"that represents the nation 's health insurers ,","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"notes","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"without subsidies ,","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"those 34 states would be in the same position as states in the 1990s","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"that passed laws","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"banning discrimination","depth":15},{"id":179,"text":"based on previous medical conditions","depth":15},{"id":180,"text":"but did nothing else .","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"`` If you look at each and every state","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"where they tried to do that ,","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"the markets blew up , ''","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"Ignagni observes .","depth":11},{"id":185,"text":"Without a mandate and subsidies","depth":14},{"id":186,"text":"to make coverage affordable ,","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"rates skyrocketed ,","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"people dropped out ,","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"and then rates skyrocketed even more","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"to cover the older , sicker people","depth":15},{"id":191,"text":"who were left .","depth":15},{"id":192,"text":"So thoroughly did the individual market collapse in some states","depth":12},{"id":193,"text":"that insurers simply refused to do business there .","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"The prospect of such chaos in the health industry ,","depth":11},{"id":195,"text":"which accounts for almost 18 percent of the U.S. economy ,","depth":11},{"id":196,"text":"is perhaps the reason","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"that business groups ,","depth":13},{"id":198,"text":"which aggressively backed Round 1 of the legal attack on Obamacare ,","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"are conspicuously missing in action on Round 2 .","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"Certainly Congress could fix the problem with a quick drafting change","depth":7},{"id":201,"text":"to make subsidies available on federal as well as state-run exchanges .","depth":7},{"id":202,"text":"But everyone knows","depth":7},{"id":203,"text":"that is n't going to happen .","depth":7},{"id":204,"text":"Congressional Republicans seem united on the idea","depth":10},{"id":205,"text":"of getting rid of Obamacare","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"- indeed , the GOP-controlled House has voted to repeal the law , in whole or in part , more than 50 times .","depth":9},{"id":207,"text":"But there is no agreement at all on what to replace it with .","depth":8},{"id":208,"text":"And in the states , some Republican governors and state legislatures are already vowing not to sign on to exchanges","depth":8},{"id":209,"text":"to save subsidies for their constituents .","depth":8},{"id":210,"text":"There is , of course , always political danger in such brinksmanship .","depth":7},{"id":211,"text":"Real people suffer the consequences .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":423,"left":0,"right":422,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":422,"left":218,"right":421,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":1,"right":217,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":217,"left":213,"right":216,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":213,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":216,"left":4,"right":215,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":5,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":421,"left":308,"right":420,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":308,"left":228,"right":307,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":8,"right":227,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":227,"left":221,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":9,"right":220,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":10,"right":219,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":219,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":13,"right":225,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":225,"left":14,"right":224,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":224,"left":15,"right":223,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":223,"left":16,"right":222,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":222,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":307,"left":274,"right":306,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":274,"left":239,"right":273,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":237,"right":238,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":237,"left":233,"right":236,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":19,"right":232,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":232,"left":20,"right":231,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":231,"left":229,"right":230,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":229,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":23,"right":24,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":25,"right":235,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":235,"left":26,"right":234,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":27,"right":28,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":29,"right":30,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":273,"left":251,"right":272,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":248,"right":250,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":241,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":31,"right":240,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":240,"left":32,"right":33,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":247,"left":242,"right":246,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":242,"left":34,"right":35,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":245,"right":40,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":245,"left":36,"right":244,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":244,"left":243,"right":39,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":243,"left":37,"right":38,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":41,"right":249,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":249,"left":42,"right":43,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":272,"left":262,"right":271,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":258,"right":261,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":255,"right":257,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":44,"right":254,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":45,"right":253,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":253,"left":46,"right":252,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":47,"right":48,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":49,"right":256,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":50,"right":51,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":261,"left":259,"right":260,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":52,"right":53,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":54,"right":55,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":271,"left":263,"right":270,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":56,"right":57,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":270,"left":58,"right":269,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":267,"right":268,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":267,"left":266,"right":63,"relation":"attribution","nucl